<subSubSection pageId="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Voss" box="[323,459,476,501]" pageId="11" refString="Voss, E. (1959) Unbekannte Curculioniden aus der orientalischen und athiopischen Region (152. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Curculioniden). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey, 10, 407 - 414." type="journal article" year="1959">Voss (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Voss, R. Borovec &amp; J. Skuhrovec" authorityYear="2017" box="[583,864,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulifer">
<emphasis box="[583,864,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="11">Trachyphloeus pustulifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<specimenCount box="[982,1136,476,501]" pageId="11" type="generic">72 specimens</specimenCount>
and compared the species with the 
<collectingRegion box="[254,319,511,536]" country="Tanzania" name="Kusini Unguja" pageId="11">South</collectingRegion>
African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall R. Borovec &amp; J. Skuhrovec" authorityYear="1923" box="[425,735,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hardenbergi">
<emphasis box="[425,735,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="11">Trachyphloeus hardenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the North African and Sicilian 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1860" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodipennis">
<emphasis box="[1156,1309,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="11">T. nodipennis</emphasis>
Chevrolat, 1860
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Seidlitz, 1868" authorityName="Seidlitz" authorityYear="1868" box="[262,540,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="godarti">
<emphasis box="[262,373,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="11">T. godarti</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Seidlitz" box="[380,540,548,573]" pageId="11" refString="Seidlitz, G. (1868) Die Otiorhynchiden s. str. nach den morphologischen Verwandtschaftsverhaltnissen ihres Hautscelet's vergleichend dargestellt. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift, 12, i - iv, 1 - 153." type="journal article" year="1868">Seidlitz, 1868</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We examined four of Voss‘ 
<typeStatus box="[866,967,549,573]" pageId="11">syntypes</typeStatus>
, on three pins, housed in the 
<collectionCode box="[1297,1384,549,572]" country="Switzerland" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1d5a-4efs" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Basel" pageId="11">NHMB</collectionCode>
, and here designate one of them as 
<typeStatus box="[500,607,583,608]" pageId="11">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The other 
<specimenCount box="[736,871,584,608]" pageId="11" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">71 syntypes</specimenCount>
are thus 
<typeStatus box="[978,1143,583,608]" pageId="11">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
. The four 
<typeStatus box="[1263,1311,584,608]" pageId="11">type</typeStatus>
specimens studied are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1906" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1906" baseAuthorityName="Marshall" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[491,851,620,645]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platycopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[491,662,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="11">P. tuberculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[674,851,620,645]" pageId="11" refString="Marshall, G. A. K. (1906) On new species of African Coleoptera of the Family Curculionidae. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 67, 911 - 958, pls. LXVI - LXVII" type="journal article" year="1906">Marshall, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described also from Transvaal, and we therefore synonymise the names 
<taxonomicName authority="Voss, 1959" authorityName="Voss, R. Borovec et J. Skuhrovec" authorityYear="1959" box="[426,849,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trachyphloeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pustulifer">
<emphasis box="[426,710,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11">Trachyphloeus pustulifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Voss" box="[722,849,655,680]" pageId="11" refString="Voss, E. (1959) Unbekannte Curculioniden aus der orientalischen und athiopischen Region (152. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Curculioniden). Entomologische Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey, 10, 407 - 414." type="journal article" year="1959">Voss, 1959</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Marshall, 1906" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1906" baseAuthorityName="Marshall" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[913,1376,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platycopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[913,1187,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="11">Platycopes tuberculatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall" box="[1199,1376,655,680]" pageId="11" refString="Marshall, G. A. K. (1906) On new species of African Coleoptera of the Family Curculionidae. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 67, 911 - 958, pls. LXVI - LXVII" type="journal article" year="1906">Marshall, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schoenherr" authorityYear="1823" box="[223,346,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platycopes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[223,346,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="11">Platycopes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently classified in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1891" box="[728,853,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Sciaphilini">Sciaphilini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
